						               													<description>The game takes place on a map of Scotland divided into 36 territories, of which 24 are assigned to specific clans. Each region has upper limits on the capacity of characters, livestock and crops.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has economic and military features. Each player starts with a single clan region and tries to gain control over additional clans by conquering more regions. The goal is to be the first to occupy a certain number of clans depending on the number of players. Conquests are made by troop movements.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To spread, players can move their pawns to neighbouring regions. Empty regions can be occupied. In occupied regions peaceful coexistence or conflicts can occur, which are then solved by figure majorities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Conquered areas are farmed and generate income in the form of money and agricultural resource yields.&amp;#10; Each clan has a knight. By participating in tournaments, which are driven by dice rolling, knights can gain weapons and shields that increase their fighting power and are thus useful in conquering, protecting and managing areas.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gameplay is divided in 3 phases (build-up, protection and endgame) with 4 seasons each.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
